<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-05T05:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-05T05:35:00-05:00" n="376" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d376">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24591/12–544: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-05T14:00:00+03:25">December 5, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 5:07 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>103. During Medjliss debate on new Cabinet,<note n="35" xml:id="d376fn35">A new Iranian Government had been formed
                                    November 26 by Morteza Qoli Bayat.</note> two or three deputies
                                criticized absence of treaty or other legal sanction for presence of
                                American troops in Iran. In his reply yesterday Premier Bay at gave
                                assurance that action would be taken to conclude a special agreement
                                on this subject at earliest possible moment.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>